OL,3,CScotland drug deaths dropped last
OL,4,Cyear, but the crisis is far from over
OL,6,FMore than 7,000 people have now died
OL,7,Fsince the Scottish government declared
OL,8,Fthis a drugs death emergency back in
OL,9,F2019.
OL,11,FThis crisis now represents what could
OL,12,Fbe the single biggest and deadliest
OL,13,Ffailure of policy in Scotland since
OL,14,Fdevolution.
OL,16,FThe problem is exacerbated in Scotland
OL,17,Fby what's known as 'polydrug use' - in
OL,18,Fother words, people taking multiple
OL,19,Fsubstances every day.
