OL,3,CScotland drug deaths dropped last
OL,4,Cyear, but the crisis is far from over
OL,6,FCalled 'The Thistle', it is a place
OL,7,Fwhere users are allowed to inject
OL,8,Ftheir own drugs in front of medically
OL,9,Ftrained staff.
OL,11,FSo far, 337 people have used the
OL,12,Fservice, and 48 medical emergencies
OL,13,Fhave been treated, with an outcome of
OL,14,Fzero deaths.
OL,16,FHaving just one drug consumption room
OL,17,Flocated in one part of Glasgow is not
OL,18,Fenough to make a dent in the national
OL,19,Fpicture for this drug death crisis,
OL,20,Fbut there are early signs it is making
OL,21,Fa difference to those who rely on it.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
